below zero.tips: Meta is still developing. Good brawlers will have high mobility for more scoring angles or ball control.

cool box.tips: Cover all lanes and prevent enemy scoring angles. Focus on getting good positioning and not throwing the match.

super center.tips: Wall break is solid for creating more goal scoring opportunities. Midrange brawlers are also good at pressuring enemy into bad positions.

belles rock.tips: Lots of gadget spam among Knockout meta. Aggression is always a threat in draft, so make sure your snipers have some counterplay or an antitank. Lookout for Rico or Darryl + Kit.

out in the open.tips: Breaking your back wall and enemy grass makes it easy to know where enemy are without getting pushed back. Lock in good snipers, only dangerous last pick is Darryl + Kit.

pinball dreams.tips: Pick brawlers with high DPS or get run down by tank + support.

double swoosh.tips: Get a wall/grass breaker to avoid getting spawn trapped by agro.

center stage.tips: Team comp needs a controller, tank, and antitank.

dueling beetles.tips: Fun but messy meta. Hot Zone is about zone time so do not use too many snipers as they easily get pushed back.

sneaky fields.tips: Lots of good brawlers to choose from such as tanks, brawlers with spammable gadgets and vision gear, etc.

hard rock mine.tips: Have a mid to hold gems, agro brawler to assassinate enemy gem carrier, and an anti tank to deal with enemy agro.

parallel plays.tips: Agro on right side, thrower/defensive brawler on left. For middle brawler get someone who can help pinch left side.

open business.tips: Map is easy to spawn trap for throwers, but also susceptible to wall break from tanks.

flaring phoenix.tips: More gadget spam, but a good variety of solid brawlers to choose from. Lookout for agro, Rosa, and Sprout for last pick.

undermine.tips: Messy meta. Controllers will be good gem carriers, tanks are good at making space and pressuring them. There are very few good anti tanks right now so tanks and healers are strong.
